        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 21 at 12:46PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 1246 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Boiling Spring Lakes, or 7 miles north of Oak Island. This
thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Oak Island, Boiling Spring Lakes, St. James, Varnamtown, and Bolivia.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
